DATA 607 Final Project

Purpose

Advanced Statistics are making a major impact in the National Hockey League. This is a professional sport where the amount of money a team can spend on average (Salary Cap Hit) is strictly limited. Therefore, decisions on how much, and how long, to pay players are crucial to a team’s success. Typically, these contract negotians include some type of ‘comparables’ where the performance of other similar players is used to set a market value. The goal for this assignment is as follows:

  1. Determine the metrics which best represent player performance as it relates to salary cap.

  2. Create a prediction function to estimate a player’s value based on the aforementioned metrics.

  3. Use the estimated player values to attempt a prediction on team success.

Necesary Functions

This function is needed to load all the tables of multi-page html files.

fill_df <- function(pages, data_df, url) {
  for(i in 2:pages){
    tmp_url <- paste0(url,i)
    players_html <- read_html(tmp_url)
    tmp_df <- as.data.frame(players_html %>% html_nodes(xpath = "//*/table[@id='brwt']") %>% html_table())
    data_df <- rbind(data_df, tmp_df)
  }
  return(data_df)
}

Player Salary Distributions

This is where the data gets a little challenging. There are actual a few different contract types in the NHL. First, there is an Entry Level Contract (ELC) where a player signs for a relatively fixed amount (typically less than one million per year for three years). Next, there is a Restricted Free Agent Contract (RFA) where a player must sign with their team, and if another team were to extend an “offer sheet” to a player to have him switch teams, it would come with additional compensation to the former team (draft picks). Finally, there are Unrestricted Free Agent Contracts (UFA) where players may sign for any amount or term (with some capped restrictions). In order to try and determine a “true” player value, this analysis tried to focus on UFA contracts by basing a filter on the expiration status of a contract (RFA, UFA) and cap hit (more than one million dollars).

ufa_player_df <- player_per_game_df[player_per_game_df$EXPIRY=="UFA" & player_per_game_df$CAP.HIT..>1000000 & player_per_game_df$GP>41 & player_per_game_df$year < 2018,]

Format Team Stats 

nst_team_stats_df <- rbind(nst_team_2015_df, nst_team_2016_df, nst_team_2017_df, nst_team_2018_df)
nst_team_stats_df$points <- nst_team_stats_df$W * 2 + nst_team_stats_df$OTL

nst_team_stats_df$teamabbr <- team_abbr_fun(nst_team_stats_df$Team)

player_per_game_df$CapxTOI <- player_per_game_df$CAP.HIT.. * player_per_game_df$TOI
player_per_game_df$EstCapxTOI <- player_per_game_df$EstCapHit * player_per_game_df$TOI
team_player_summary_df <- player_per_game_df %>% filter(GP>10) %>% mutate(countcolumn = 1) %>% group_by(Team, year) %>% summarize(weighted = sum(CapxTOI), estweighted = sum(EstCapxTOI), captotal = sum(CAP.HIT..), time = sum(TOI), players = sum(countcolumn)) %>% mutate(weighted_cap = weighted / time) %>% mutate(est_weighted_cap = estweighted / time) %>% mutate(cap = captotal / sum(players))
keep <- c("teamabbr", "year", "GP","points", "PDO", "SV.", "W", "CF.", "FF.", "SF.", "LDSV.", "MDSV.", "HDSV.", "GF", "GP", "HDCF")
team_summary_df <- merge(team_player_summary_df, nst_team_stats_df[,names(nst_team_stats_df) %in% keep], by.x = c("Team", "year"), by.y = c("teamabbr", "year")) %>% mutate(year = factor(year))
team_past_summary_df <- team_summary_df %>% filter(year!=2018)

Prediction 

season_home_adv_df <- season_schedule_df %>% filter(Date<Sys.Date()) %>% mutate(winner = ifelse(G.1 - G > 0, "H", "V"), count = 1) %>% group_by(winner) %>% summarize(count = sum(count))
home_adv = season_home_adv_df[season_home_adv_df$winner=="H",c("count")][[1]] / (season_home_adv_df[season_home_adv_df$winner=="V",c("count")][[1]])

season_ot_chance_df <- season_schedule_df %>% filter(Date<Sys.Date()) %>% mutate(ot = ifelse(Var.6=="OT" | Var.6=="SO","Y","N"), count = 1) %>% group_by(ot) %>% summarize(count = sum(count))
ot_chance <- season_ot_chance_df[season_ot_chance_df$ot=="Y",c("count")][[1]] / (season_ot_chance_df[season_ot_chance_df$ot=="Y",c("count")][[1]] + season_ot_chance_df[season_ot_chance_df$ot=="N",c("count")][[1]]) 

season_remaining_schedule_df <- season_schedule_df[,c("Date", "Visitor", "Home")] %>% filter(Date>Sys.Date())
season_remaining_schedule_df$Visitor_Abbr <- team_abbr_fun(season_remaining_schedule_df$Visitor)
season_remaining_schedule_df$Home_Abbr <- team_abbr_fun(season_remaining_schedule_df$Home)
season_remaining_schedule_df$Visitor_Weighted_Cap <- unname(unlist(sapply(season_remaining_schedule_df$Visitor_Abbr, function(x) {team_summary_df[team_summary_df$Team==x & team_summary_df$year==2018,c("est_weighted_cap")]})))
season_remaining_schedule_df$Home_Weighted_Cap <- unname(unlist(sapply(season_remaining_schedule_df$Home_Abbr, function(x) {team_summary_df[team_summary_df$Team==x & team_summary_df$year==2018,c("est_weighted_cap")]})))
season_remaining_schedule_df$Home_Weighted_Cap_Adj <- season_remaining_schedule_df$Home_Weighted_Cap * home_adv
season_remaining_schedule_df$Combined_Cap = season_remaining_schedule_df$Home_Weighted_Cap + season_remaining_schedule_df$Visitor_Weighted_Cap
#set.seed(2343)
season_remaining_schedule_df$ValuePicked <- sapply(season_remaining_schedule_df$Combined_Cap, function(x) {runif(1, 1, x)})
season_remaining_schedule_df$Winner <- ifelse(season_remaining_schedule_df$ValuePicked < season_remaining_schedule_df$Home_Weighted_Cap_Adj, season_remaining_schedule_df$Home_Abbr, season_remaining_schedule_df$Visitor_Abbr)
season_remaining_schedule_df$OT <- ifelse(season_remaining_schedule_df$Winner==season_remaining_schedule_df$Home_Abbr & season_remaining_schedule_df$ValuePicked > season_remaining_schedule_df$Home_Weighted_Cap_Adj - season_remaining_schedule_df$Combined_Cap * ot_chance/2, season_remaining_schedule_df$Visitor_Abbr,
                                          ifelse(season_remaining_schedule_df$Winner==season_remaining_schedule_df$Visitor_Abbr & season_remaining_schedule_df$ValuePicked < season_remaining_schedule_df$Home_Weighted_Cap_Adj + season_remaining_schedule_df$Combined_Cap * ot_chance/2, season_remaining_schedule_df$Home_Abbr, NA))

season_remaining_summary_df <- season_remaining_schedule_df %>% group_by(Winner, OT) %>% mutate(count = 1) %>% summarize(results = sum(count)) %>% gather(type, team, 1:2, na.rm = TRUE) %>% mutate(points = ifelse(type=="Winner",2*results,1*results)) %>% group_by(team) %>% summarize(points = sum(points))
